---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../../components/PageHero.astro';
import Section from '../../../components/Section.astro';

import cambriaHero from '../../../assets/cambria-hero.jpg';

/*
 * 1:1 reproduction of the live gsuair.com/cambria-county-gov page: same
 * headings, same copy, same order — nothing added, nothing removed.
 *
 * Copy is verbatim, including the live page's own quirks: it calls the company
 * "Germ Solution Service USA" throughout (not "Germ Solutions USA"), it leaves
 * in the drafting aside "Here's a detailed breakdown based on the provided
 * information:", and the closing paragraph has no full stop.
 */
---

<Base
  title="Lehigh, York, & Cambria Counties' Correctional Facilities"
  description="PA prison facilities find solution for their poor indoor air quality — InductPro Series purification and Indoor Air Quality Monitoring System 360 across three county correctional facilities."
>
  <PageHero
    title="LEHIGH, YORK, & CAMBRIA COUNTIES' CORRECTIONAL FACILITIES"
    image={cambriaHero}
    imageAlt="Interior of a correctional facility"
  />

  <Section tone="tint" title="PA PRISON FACILITIES FIND SOLUTION FOR THEIR POOR INDOOR AIR QUALITY">
    <div class="mt-8 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
        Germ Solution Service USA has taken significant steps to enhance safety measures within the prison facilities of
        Lehigh, York , and Cambria Counties in Pennsylvania. Here's a detailed breakdown based on the provided
        information:
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="brand" title="Installation of Air & Surface Purification Systems">
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-brand-100">
        Germ Solution Service USA has installed their InductPro Series devices within the ductwork of the mentioned
        prison facilities. These devices are designed to release molecules that actively target and disable COVID-19 and
        other pathogens present in the air and on surfaces. By integrating these systems into the existing
        infrastructure, the company aims to create a safer environment for staff, inmates and visitors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="tint" title="Implementation of Indoor Air Quality Monitoring System 360">
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
      <p>
        In addition to the purification systems, Germ Solution Service USA has installed their Indoor Air Quality
        Monitoring System 360. This technology enables prison administrators to continuously monitor the air quality
        within the facilities in real-time. This proactive approach allows for early detection of any potential issues
        and ensures prompt action can be taken to maintain a healthy indoor environment.
      </p>
      <p>
        To demonstrate the effectiveness of the installed systems, each facility will undergo 12 months of pathogen
        testing. This comprehensive testing process will provide valuable data on the reduction of pathogens, including
        COVID-19, within the prison environment. By conducting this testing over an extended period, Germ Solution
        Service USA aims to showcase the long-term benefits and efficacy of their solutions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Overall, Germ Solution Service USA's initiatives demonstrate a commitment to leveraging innovative technologies
        to address the challenges posed by COVID-19 and other pathogens within prison facilities. By combining
        purification systems with real-time monitoring and thorough testing protocols, they are contributing to the
        creation of safer and healthier environments for all stakeholders involved
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Base>
